0Express%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20report%20prepared%20by%20the%2030-member%20committee%20headed%20by%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20MP%20Brij%20Lal%2C%20suggests%20many%20changes%20in%20the%20Bills.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESeveral%20members%2C%20including%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20Adhir%20Ranjan%20Chowdhury%2C%20Digvijaya%20Singh%20and%20Dravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam%E2%80%99s%20(DMK%E2%80%99s)%20N.%20R.%20Elango%2C%20have%20already%20submitted%20dissent%20notes.%20Others%2C%20including%20former%20Union%20home%20minister%20P.%20Chidambaram%20sought%20an%20extension%20till%20Thursday%20to%20submit%20their%20dissent%20notes%20but%20the%20committee%20stuck%20to%20its%20earlier%20deadline%20of%20Wednesday%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fparliament-panel-adopts-reports-on-criminal-laws%2Farticleshow%2F105007674.cms%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOpposition%20sources%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fstanding-panel-adopts-reports-on-criminal-laws-9016462%2F%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%3Cem%3E%20Indian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20Chidambaram%20along%20with%20All%20India%20Trinamool%20Congress%20(TMC)%20members%20Derek%20O%E2%80%99%20Brien%20and%20Kakoli%20Ghosh%20Dastidar%20would%20submit%20detailed%20dissent%20notes%20and%20that%20all%2010%20opposition%20members%20in%20the%20panel%20would%20submit%20separate%20dissent%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fthe-three-criminal-law-bills-using-criminal-law-to-establish-permanent-extra-constitutional-emergency-powers%5C%22%3EThe%20Three%20Criminal%20Law%20Bills%3A%20Using%20Criminal%20Law%20to%20Establish%20Permanent%20Extra-Constitutional%20Emergency%20Powers%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESome%20opposition%20members%2C%20including%20DMK%E2%80%99s%20Dayanidhi%20Maran%2C%20are%20said%20to%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fstanding-panel-adopts-reports-on-criminal-laws-9016462%2F%5C%22%3Eopposed%20the%20usage%20of%20Hindi%20in%20the%20Bills%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20it%20goes%20against%20the%20spirit%20of%20the%20constitution.%20However%2C%20the%20committee%20has%20not%20recommended%20a%20change%20of%20names%20or%20English%20versions%20of%20the%20names%20in%20its%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESome%20members%20were%20also%20not%20in%20favour%20of%20bringing%20terror%2C%20corruption%20and%20organised%20crime%20under%20the%20new%20penal%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOther%20recommendations%20made%20by%20members%20include%20having%20a%20comprehensive%20definition%20of%20community%20service%20and%20what%20it%20would%20entail%20as%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20%E2%80%93%20which%20seeks%20to%20replace%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20%E2%80%93%20prescribes%20community%20service%20as%20an%20alternate%20form%20of%20punishment%20for%20some%20minor%20offences.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fparliament-panel-adopts-reports-on-criminal-laws%2Farticleshow%2F105007674.cms%5C%22%3Ethe%20committee%20has%20backed%20a%20gender-neutral%20adultery%20law%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20punitive%20measures%20for%20non-consensual%20sex%20between%20men%2C%20women%20and%20transgender%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20also%20proposed%20a%20reduction%20in%20sentence%20for%20those%20convicted%20of%20deterring%20public%20servants%20from%20discharging%20their%20duties.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20paper%2C%20the%20committee%20has%20also%20recommended%20slashing%20the%20maximum%20prison%20term%20under%20Section%20353%20of%20the%20IPC%20from%20two%20years%20to%20one%20%E2%80%93%20citing%20that%20the%20law%20is%20often%20used%20against%20protesters%20and%20many%20members%20of%20the%20committee%20are%20of%20the%20view%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fparliament-panel-adopts-reports-on-criminal-laws%2Farticleshow%2F105007674.cms%5C%22%3Ecommon%20protesters%20should%20be%20dealt%20with%20leniently%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20will%20be%20placed%20before%20parliament%20once%20the%20winter%20session%20begins%2C%20NDTV%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fparliamentary-panel-greenlights-bills-to-change-indias-criminal-laws-4551514%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699340102000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F02%2F11082632%2FImage6.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fparliamentary-panel-adopts-reports-on-three-criminal-bills-several-dissent-notes-from-opposition%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20report%20prepared%20by%20the%2030-member%20committee%20has%20suggested%20many%20changes%20in%20the%20three%20Bills.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fparliamentary-panel-adopts-reports-on-three-criminal-bills-several-dissent-notes-from-opposition%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Pooja%20shares%20inside%20PICS%20from%20Raha's%20birthday%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699340082000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105031874%2Cimgsize-264014.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fpooja-bhatt-shares-pic-of-dad-mahesh-bhatt-on-niece-rahas-first-birthday-calls-it-the-circle-of-life-see-inside%2Farticleshow%2F105031925.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F105031925.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EEarlier%2C%20Alia%20treated%