20recover%20from%20the%20effects%20of%20Covid-19%20on%20the%20economy%20and%20its%20failed%20initial%20public%20offering%20in%202019.%20The%20New%20York-based%20corporation%20filed%20a%20Chapter%2011%20filing%20in%20New%20Jersey%2C%20stating%20that%20its%20assets%20and%20liabilities%20were%20between%20%2410%20billion%20and%20%2450%20billion.%20The%20filing%20allows%20WeWork%20to%20keep%20operating%20while%20it%20works%20out%20a%20plan%20to%20repay%20its%20debts.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAdam%20Neumann%2C%20the%20former%20CEO%20of%20WeWork%20founded%20the%20company%20in%202010%20and%20by%202019%2C%20it%20was%20worth%20%2447%20billion.%20He%20stated%20that%20the%20bankruptcy%20filing%20is%20%26quot%3Bdisappointing%26quot%3B%20and%20it%20has%20been%20hard%20for%20him%20to%20watch%20the%20company%20struggle.%20However%2C%20the%2044-year-old%20most%20certainly%20still%20has%20a%20large%20net%20worth%2C%20in%20contrast%20to%20many%20founders%20whose%20fortunes%20have%20vanished%20along%20with%20their%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhen%20Mr%20Neumann%20left%20the%20company%2C%20a%20significant%20amount%20of%20wealth%20was%20accumulated%20as%20it%20prepared%20for%20another%20public%20offering-%20time%20through%20a%20special%20purpose%20acquisition%20company%20(SPAC).%20In%202021%2C%20Mr%20Neumann%20reportedly%20received%20%24480%20million%20from%20SoftBank%20for%20half%20of%20his%20remaining%20WeWork%20stock%20as%20part%20of%20that%20SPAC%20process.%20He%20filed%20a%20lawsuit%20after%20the%20investment%20giant%20first%20tried%20to%20back%20out%20of%20purchasing%20the%20entirety%20of%20his%20%241%20billion%20stake%2C%20as%20per%20a%20report%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2023%2F11%2F07%2Fheres-how-much-wework-founder-adam-neumann-got-before-bankruptcy.html%5C%22%3ECNBC%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20reports%2C%20Mr%20Neumann%20also%20received%20an%20additional%20%24185%20million%20as%20payment%20for%20a%20non-compete%20agreement%20and%20an%20additional%20%24106%20million%20as%20settlement.%20Overall%2C%20it%20is%20believed%20that%20Mr%20Neumann%20made%20over%20%24770%20million%20in%20cash%20from%20the%202021%20SPAC%20process%20alone%2C%20despite%20having%20been%20removed%20from%20a%20management%20position%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20Bloomberg%2C%20when%20WeWork%20debuted%20in%202021%2C%20the%20former%20CEO%20still%20had%20a%20stake%20in%20the%20company%20valued%20at%20%24722%20million.%20Although%20it%20is%20unclear%20as%20to%20how%20many%20shares%20he%20owns%20currently%2C%20all%20those%20have%20become%20%26quot%3Bworthless%26quot%3B%20after%20the%20bankruptcy%20filing.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDiscussing%20the%20company's%20bankruptcy%2C%20Mr%20Neumann%20told%20CNBC%20in%20a%20statement%2C%20%26quot%3BAs%20the%20co-founder%20of%20WeWork%20who%20spent%20a%20decade%20building%20the%20business%20with%20an%20amazing%20team%20of%20mission-driven%20people%2C%20the%20company's%20anticipated%20bankruptcy%20filing%20is%20disappointing.%20It%20has%20been%20challenging%20for%20me%20to%20watch%20from%20the%20sidelines%20since%202019%20as%20WeWork%20has%20failed%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20a%20product%20that%20is%20more%20relevant%20today%20than%20ever%20before.%20I%20believe%20that%2C%20with%20the%20right%20strategy%20and%20team%2C%20a%20reorganization%20will%20enable%20WeWork%20to%20emerge%20successfully.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699337400000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-11%2Foh92jb7o_wework-founder_625x300_07_November_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwework-wework-bankruptcy-this-is-how-much-wework-founder-earned-before-it-filed-for-bankruptcy-4552774%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Adam%20Neumann%2C%20the%20former%20CEO%20of%20WeWork%20founded%20the%20company%20in%202010%20and%20by%202019%2C%20it%20was%20worth%20%2447%20billion.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https