didates%20across%20all%20the%20Scheduled%20Tribe%20seats%20in%20the%20state.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20hope%20our%20candidates%20win.%20But%20even%20otherwise%2C%20we%20will%20surely%20damage%20the%20vote%20count%20for%20the%20parties%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fchhattisgarh-in-chandameta-with-electricity-roads-and-water-a-polling-booth-for-the-first-time%5C%22%3EChhattisgarh%3A%20In%20Chandameta%2C%20With%20Electricity%2C%20Roads%20and%20Water%20%E2%80%93%20a%20Polling%20Booth%20for%20the%20First%20Time%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20most%20interesting%20election%20in%20the%20Bastar%20region%2C%20however%2C%20is%20being%20fought%20in%20Sukma%2C%20one%20of%20the%20still%20red%20districts%20in%20the%20red%20corridor.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%20Sukma%20district%E2%80%99s%20Konta%2C%20the%20Congress%20candidate%20Kawasi%20Lakhma%20is%20facing%20stiff%20opposition%20from%20his%20constituency.%20The%20cabinet%20minister%20has%20had%20to%20face%20severe%20criticism%20in%20Konta%20over%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20handling%20of%20various%20protests%2C%20including%20Silger%2C%20which%20lasted%20for%20more%20than%20a%20year.%20On%20May%2017%2C%202021%2C%20four%20tribals%20were%20shot%20dead%20by%20security%20forces%20after%20they%20opened%20fire%20on%20a%20protesting%20mob.%20The%20mob%20of%20residents%20from%20nearby%20villages%20were%20protesting%20against%20a%20security%20camp.%20While%20police%20maintained%20that%20the%20protests%20were%20on%20the%20behest%20of%20Maoists%2C%20the%20locals%20protested%20on%20the%20site%20of%20conflict%20in%20huge%20numbers.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F05%2F17105859%2FScreenshot-2022-05-17-at-10.58.13-AM.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F05%2F17105859%2FScreenshot-2022-05-17-at-10.58.13-AM.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F05%2F17105859%2FScreenshot-2022-05-17-at-10.58.13-AM-300x190.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F05%2F17105859%2FScreenshot-2022-05-17-at-10.58.13-AM-1024x648.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-597022%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22759%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EFile%20image%20of%20a%202022%20protest%20march%20at%20Silger%2C%20in%20Sukma%20of%20Chhattisgarh.%20Photo%3A%20Special%20arrangement%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%20election%2C%20the%20prominent%20candidate%20from%20Sukma%20was%20Manish%20Kunjam%2C%20an%20ex-MLA%20from%20CPI.%20While%20his%20rallies%20were%20drawing%20many%20people%20he%20had%20alleged%20that%20the%20district%20machinery%20had%20been%20trying%20to%20stop%20him%20from%20visiting%20villages%2C%20citing%20%E2%80%9Csecurity%20reasons%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CWhy%20are%20there%20so%20many%20camps%20if%20they%20can%E2%80%99t%20provide%20me%20enough%20security%20to%20meet%20the%20villagers%2C%20like%20common%20men%3F%20It%20is%20a%20planned%20mission%20of%20the%20MLA%20along%20with%20district%20officials%2C%20to%20stop%20me%20reaching%20parts%20of%20my%20constituency%20where%20people%20are%20full%20of%20anger%20against%20him%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20had%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EKunjam%2C%20however%2C%20faced%20the%20first%20fall%20after%20his%20party%20symbol%20was%20changed%20from%20the%20CPI%E2%80%99s%20well%20known%20hammer%20and%20sickle%20to%20an%20air%20conditioner.%20The%20symbol%20was%20allotted%20to%20him%20after%20the%20party%20realised%20that%20they%20had%20forgotten