nging%20for%20me%20to%20watch%20from%20the%20sidelines%20since%202019%20as%20WeWork%20has%20failed%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20a%20product%20that%20is%20more%20relevant%20today%20than%20ever%20before%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businesswire.com%2Fnews%2Fhome%2F20231106843900%2Fen%2FStatement-From-WeWork-Co-Founder-Adam-Neumann%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIt%2520has%2520been%2520challenging%2520for%2Cenable%2520WeWork%2520to%2520emerge%2520successfully%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epress%20release%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BI%20believe%20that%2C%20with%20the%20right%20strategy%20and%20team%2C%20a%20reorganization%20will%20enable%20WeWork%20to%20emerge%20successfully.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20its%20peak%2C%20the%20company%20was%20valued%20at%20%2447%20billion%20as%20a%20private%20company.%20But%20the%20startup%20has%20been%20in%20turmoil%20ever%20since%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fweworks-nightmare-ipo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplans%20to%20go%20public%20in%202019%20fell%20apart%3C%2Fa%3E%20amid%20concerns%20about%20the%20company's%20profitability%20and%20some%20of%20Neumann's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployees-inside-adam-neumanns-wework-reveal-a-wild-culture-2019-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einappropriate%20antics%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJapanese%20investor%20SoftBank%20has%20dropped%20billions%20of%20dollars%20into%20the%20real%20estate%20startup%20and%20remains%20its%20majority%20shareholder.%20Yet%2C%20WeWork%20has%20never%20turned%20a%20profit.%20In%20the%20first%20half%20of%20the%20year%2C%20the%20company%20lost%20%24696%20million%2C%20per%20its%20most%20recent%20earnings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%202019%2C%20the%20company's%20valuation%20has%20continued%20to%20fall.%20In%20April%2C%20prices%20dropped%20below%20%241%20per%20share%20and%20it%20faced%20the%20potential%20of%20being%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwework-startup-failure-benchmark-insight-partners-venture-capitalists-learned-nothing-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Edelisted%20from%20the%20New%20York%20Stock%20Exchange%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20in%20August%2C%20WeWork%20said%20it%20had%20%26quot%3Bsubstantial%20doubt%26quot%3B%20it%20would%20be%20able%20to%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwework-has-substantial-doubt-about-continue-to-operate-going-concern-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cu%3Estay%20in%20business%20much%20longer%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWeWork's%20bankruptcy%20comes%20amidst%20a%20years-long%20reorientation%20for%20the%20office%20industry.%20Commercial%20real%20estate%20companies%20have%20struggled%20to%20recover%20from%20the%20pandemic's%20seismic%20shift%20to%20remote%20work%20that%20weakened%20office%20demand%20worldwide%2C%20even%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20many%20companies%20shifting%20to%20a%20hybrid%20model%20or%20demanding%20employees%20return%20to%20the%20office%20full-time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBankruptcy%20might%20not%20be%20the%20end%20for%20WeWork%2C%20which%20currently%20operates%20over%20300%20locations%20worldwide.%20The%20Chapter%2011%20process%20allows%20companies%20to%20shed%20some%20debt%20and%20reorganize.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E(WeWork%20competitor%20Regus%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.globest.com%2Fsites%2Fglobest%2F2003%2F01%2F15%2Fregus-us-files-for-chapter-11-protection%2F%3Fslreturn%3D20231006152739%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efiled%20for%20bankruptcy%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20US%20in%202003%20and%20has%20continued%20to%20operate%20successfully.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWait%2C%20wasn't%20WeWork%20already%20in%20trouble%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company's%20failed%20attempt%20to%20go%20public%20in%202019%20made%20it%20the%20laughing%20stock%20of%20the%20business%20world%20%E2%80%94%20and%20led%20to%20a%20big%20financial%20life%20r