e%20ministry%20said%2C%20releasing%20video%20footage%20it%20said%20was%20from%20the%20test.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20test%20involved%20the%20firing%20of%20an%20intercontinental-range%20Bulava%20submarine-launched%20ballistic%20missile%20(SLBM)%20and%20was%20a%20significant%20step%20for%20the%20vessel.%20Decisions%20on%20the%20submarine's%20entry%20into%20service%20with%20the%20Russian%20navy%20will%20follow%20this%20test%2C%20the%20last%20of%20the%20state%20trials%2C%20Russia%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVideo%20footage%20from%20the%20defense%20ministry%20that%20was%20shared%20by%20Russian%20state%20media%20outlets%20on%20Sunday%20showed%20what%20they%20said%20was%20the%20newest%20Borei-class%20nuclear-powered%20ballistic%20missile%20submarine%20Imperator%20Alexander%20III%20launching%20an%20RSM-56%20Bulava%20ballistic%20missile.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20video%2C%20the%20missile%20flies%20up%20and%20soars%20across%20the%20sky%2C%20leaving%20a%20large%20trail%20of%20smoke%20behind%20it.%20Russia's%20defense%20ministry%20said%20that%20the%20test%20took%20place%20in%20the%20White%20Sea%20off%20Russia's%20northern%20coast%2C%20with%20the%20missile%20hitting%20a%20target%20on%20the%20Kura%20combat%20field%20on%20the%20far%20eastern%20Kamchatka%20peninsula.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22twitter%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%20%3Cblockquote%20data-lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%20data-conversation%3D%5C%22undefined%5C%22%20data-cards%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%20%E2%80%94Sputnik%20(%40SputnikInt)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fmims%2Fstatuses%2F1721023549198958819%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3ENovember%205%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20purportedly%20successful%20test%20was%20an%20important%20%E2%80%94%20and%20final%20%E2%80%94%20step%20for%20the%20Imperator%20Alexander%20III.%20%26quot%3BMissile%20warheads%20arrived%20in%20the%20designated%20area%20at%20the%20set%20time.%20The%20ballistic%20missile%20firing%20is%20the%20final%20element%20of%20state%20trials%2C%20with%20the%20decision%20to%20be%20made%20after%20that%20on%20cruiser's%20acceptance%20by%20the%20Navy%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20ministry%20said%20in%20the%20statement%20published%20by%20state%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20it%20enters%20service%2C%20it'll%20be%20the%20seventh%20and%20latest%20of%20Russia's%20Project%20955%20Borei-class%20submarines%20to%20do%20so%20and%20only%20the%20fourth%20of%20the%20newer%2C%20more%20modern%20955As.%20These%20ballistic%20missile%20submarines%20have%20been%20in%20service%20with%20the%20Russian%20navy%20since%202013%2C%20and%20the%20most%20recent%20boat%20in%20the%20class%20to%20join%20the%20fleet%20was%20the%20Generalissimus%20Suvorov%2C%20which%20was%20commissioned%20in%20late%20December%202022.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224042%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russian%20nuclear%20submarine%20Yuri%20Dolgorukiy%20(NATO%20reporting%20name%3A%20SSBN%20%26quot%3BBorei%26quot%3B%2C%20or%20%26quot%3BDolgorukiy%26quot%3B)%20is%20seen%20during%20the%20Navy%20Day%20Military%20parade%20July%2C%2027%2C%202014%2C%20in%20Severomorsk.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654944643cc84b4dfafd3ed5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222614%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERussian%20nuclear%20submarine%20Yuri%20Dolgorukiy%20(NATO%20reporting%20name%3A%20SSBN%20%26quot%3BBorei%26quot%3B%2C%20or%20%26quot%3BDolgorukiy%26quot%3B)%20is%20seen%20during%20the%20Navy%20Day%20Military%20parade%20July%2C%2027%2C%202014%2C%20in%20Severomorsk.%3Cp%3ESasha%20Mordovets%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20more%20modern%20subs%2C%20like%20Imperator%20Alexander%20III%20and%20Generalissimus%20Suvorov%2C%20are%20designed%20to%20carry%20as%20many%20as%2016%20Bulava%20SLBMs%2C%20which%20have%20been%20in%20service%20since%20a%20series%20of%20successful%20tests%20in%202018%20and%20are%20a%20powerf