Fen%2Faustralia%2Ft-18172340%5C%22%3EAustralian%3C%2Fa%3E%20prime%20minister%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fchina%2Ft-18480887%5C%22%3Ethe%20People%E2%80%99s%20Republic%20of%20China%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlbanese%20on%20Monday%20stopped%20by%20the%20Temple%20of%20Heaven%20in%20Beijing%2C%20following%20in%20the%20footsteps%20of%20the%20first%20Australian%20leader%2C%C2%A0Gough%20Whitlam%2C%20who%20visited%20China%20five%20decades%20ago%20as%20ties%20between%20the%20two%20countries%20were%20being%20established.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSince%20he%20visited%20the%20Temple%20of%20Heaven%20in%20Beijing%20much%20has%20changed.%20But%20what%20is%20constant%20is%20that%20engagement%20between%20our%20two%20countries%20remains%20important%2C%E2%80%9D%20Albanese%20said%20in%20a%20post%20on%20X%2C%20formerly%20known%20as%20Twitter.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20did%20Xi%20and%20Albanese%20say%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlbanese%20highlighted%20Beijing%E2%80%99s%20lifting%20of%20some%20restrictions%20on%20Australian%20products%20since%20his%20first%20meeting%20with%20Xi%20in%C2%A0Indonesia%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20progress%20we%20have%20made%20in%20advancing%20our%20relationship%20over%20that%20time%20has%20been%20unquestionably%20very%20positive%2C%E2%80%9D%20Albanese%20said%20in%20opening%20remarks%20to%20Xi%20before%20the%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWith%C2%A0Beijing%20being%C2%A0Canberra%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20trading%20partner%2C%20the%20focus%20of%20Albanese%E2%80%99s%20visit%20has%20been%20on%20trade%20discussions.%20This%20includes%20easing%20barriers%20that%20have%20impacted%20Australian%20exports%20by%20billions%20of%20dollars%20and%20seeking%20consensus%20on%20how%20to%20settle%20future%20trade%20disputes.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EXi%20said%20that%20both%20sides%20had%20resumed%20exchanges%20of%20views%20and%20worked%20out%20some%20problems.%3Cbr%3E%20%E2%80%9CThe%20China-Australia%20relationship%20has%20embarked%20on%20the%20right%20path%20of%20improvement%20and%20development%2C%E2%80%9D%20Xi%20said.%20%E2%80%9CI%E2%80%99m%20heartened%20to%20see%20that.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20their%20meeting%2C%20Albanese%20said%20he%20walked%20away%20from%20the%20talks%20%E2%80%9Csatisfied%20that%20we%20have%20positive%20engagement%20between%20Australia%20and%20China.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20told%20reporters%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cconflict%20in%20the%20world%20was%20raised%2C%E2%80%9D%20including%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20and%20the%20Israel-Hamas%20war%20in%20the%20context%20of%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20need%20for%20peace%20and%20security%20in%20our%20region.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20spoke%20about%20guardrails%20and%20military-to-military%20cooperation%20between%20the%20United%20States%20and%20China%3B%20that%E2%80%99s%20important%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EChinese%20media%20reported%20that%20Xi%20told%20Albanese%20on%20Monday%20that%20China%20and%20Australia%C2%A0stood%20to%20become%20%E2%80%9Ctrusting%20partners%E2%80%9D%20and%20were%20on%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccorrect%20path%20of%20improving%20and%20developing%20relations.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20the%C2%A0significance%20of%20Albanese%E2%80%99s%20trip%20to%20China%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EChina%20and%20Australia%E2%80%99s%20relations%20have%20seen%20rising%20tensions%20since%202017%2C%20with%20Canberra%20suspecting%20Chinese%20intervention%20in%20Australian%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Australian%20government%20later%20barred%C2%A0Chinese%20tech%20giant%20Huawei%20from%205G%20contracts.%20Australia%20had%20also%20called%20for%20an%20inquest%20into%20the%20origins%20of%20the%20coronavirus%2C%20angering%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBeijing%20then%20imposed%C2%A0punitive%20tariffs%20on%20a%20slew%20of%20Australian%20commodities%2C%20and%C2%A0tensions%20continued%20to%20escalate%20over%20the%20detention%20of%20Australian