e%20Better%20India%20(%40thebetterindia)%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%20%3Cp%3EBut%20introducing%20this%20South%20Indian%20culinary%20delight%20in%20the%20Northeastern%20state%20was%20not%20easy.%20%E2%80%9CInitially%2C%20I%20went%20door%20to%20door%20of%20various%20restaurants%20with%20samples%20and%20requested%20people%20to%20try%20our%20%3Cem%3Eparatha%3C%2Fem%3Es.%20At%20first%2C%20they%20would%20be%20reluctant.%20But%20then%20I%20would%20make%20the%20%3Cem%3Eparatha%3C%2Fem%3E%20within%20a%20few%20minutes%20and%20serve%20it%20to%20them%20with%20curry.%20Whoever%20tasted%20it%20appreciated%20the%20quality%20and%20the%20taste%20of%20my%20%3Cem%3Eparathas%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Soon%2C%20many%20more%20people%20started%20adding%20this%20dish%20to%20their%20menus%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPriced%20at%20Rs%2060%20and%20Rs%20100%2C%20these%20packaged%20%3Cem%3Eparatha%3C%2Fem%3Es%20come%20in%20packs%20of%20five%20or%2010%20pieces.%20They%20have%20a%20shelf%20life%20of%20three%20days%2C%20which%20extends%20up%20to%20seven%20days%20if%20stored%20in%20refrigerators.%20It%20has%20become%20a%20good%20choice%20for%20working%20professionals.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAssam-based%20Akhilesh%20Gupta%2C%20who%20runs%20a%20tea%20stall%2C%20loves%20these%20parathas.%20He%20tells%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%2C%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%E2%80%9CAlthough%20this%20was%20a%20new%20kind%20of%20%3Cem%3Eparatha%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20we%20absolutely%20loved%20it.%20It%20has%20so%20many%20layers%20and%20is%20so%20soft%20to%20eat.%20We%20keep%20a%20stock%20of%20it%2C%20and%20whenever%20we%20run%20out%20of%20wheat%20at%20home%2C%20these%20%3Cem%3Eparatha%3C%2Fem%3Es%20come%20to%20our%20rescue.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20Diganta%2C%20this%20experience%20helped%20him%20battle%20poverty%20and%20build%20the%20life%20he%20desired%20for%20his%20family.%20%E2%80%9CI%20was%20not%20qualified%20enough%20to%20get%20a%20high-salaried%20job.%20I%20was%20always%20reluctant%20to%20do%20farming%2C%20so%20I%20always%20ran%20from%20city%20to%20city%20doing%20menial%20jobs.%20I%20am%20glad%20that%20I%20was%20able%20to%20climb%20the%20ladder%20of%20success%20right%20from%20the%20place%20where%20it%20all%20started%20%E2%80%94%20my%20village%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Edited%20by%20Pranita%20Bhat%3B%20All%20photos%3A%20Diganta%20Das)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESource%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ijrte.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fpapers%2Fv9i1%2FA2777059120.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFactors%20and%20Impact%20of%20Rural%20Out-Migration%20in%20Assam%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20Published%20by%20Blue%20Eyes%20Intelligence%20Engineering%20%26amp%3B%20Sciences%20Publication%20in%202020.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699021876000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D333562%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20security%20guard%20in%20Bengaluru%2C%20Assam's%20Diganta%20Das%20returned%20to%20his%20village%20and%20launched%20his%20own%20startup%20to%20sell%20the%20popular%20Malabar%20parottas.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Shivani%20Gupta%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A44%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Swimmer%20Escaped%20the%20British%20in%20the%20Ganga%2C%20Suffered%20Bullet%20Wound%20%26amp%3B%20Won%20Gold%20For%20India%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EMillions%20of%20Indians%20joined%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F263172%2Fmahatma-gandhi-jayanti-best-quotes-inspiring-heroes-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMohandas%20Karamchand%20(Mahatma)%20Gandhi%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99s%20call%20for%20mass%20civil%20disobedience%20against%20British%20colonial%20rule%20in%201930.%20Popularly%20known%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F155445%2Fkhurshed-framji-nariman-mumbai-news%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECivil%20Disobedience%20Movement%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20was%20marked%20by%20protest%20rallies%20across%20a%20plethora%20of%20villages%2C%20towns%20and%20cities.%20Among%20the%20millions%20who%20participated%20in%20this%20landmark%20movement%20was%20a%2010-year-old%20boy.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAttending%20a%20public%20rally%20along%20the%20banks%20of%20the%20Ganga%20in%20Varanasi%2C%20a%20holy%20city%20in%20present-day%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20this%20young%20boy%20got%20caught%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20a%20police%20crackdown.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20they%20began%20lathi-charging%20protestors%2C%20this%2010-year-old%20boy%20%E2%80%9Cjumped%20into%20the%20River%20Ganges%20to%20hide%20from%20the%20police%20in%20between%20the%20boats%E2%80%9D%20and%20hid%20underwater.%20Meanwhile%2C%20as%20a%202014%20media%20report%20notes%2C%20%E2%80%9Ca%2010%20km%20swimming%20competition%20was%20going%20on%20over%20the%20Ganges.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTo%20hide%20himself%2C%20he%20also%20joined%20the%20competition%20group%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20goes%20on%20to%20add.%20To%20everyone%E2%80%99s%20bewilderment%2C%20he%20finished%20third%20in%20this%20race.%20It%20was%20the%20start%20of%20something%20special.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20young%20boy%E2%80%99s%20name%20was%20Sachin%20Nag%2C%20a%20legendary%20swimming%20champion%20and%20gold%20medal%20winner%20in%20the%20men%E2%80%99s%20100%20m%20freestyle%20event%20at%20the%201951%20Asian%20Games%20in%20New%20Delhi.%20Till%20today%2C%20it%20remains%20India%E2%80%99s%20only%20gold%20medal%20in%20swimming%20events%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F331761%2Fram-baboo-daily-wager-uttar-pradesh-wins-bronze-medal-in-asian-games-video%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAsian%20Games%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EFor%20the%20love%20of%20swimming%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EBorn%20into%20a%20Bengali%20family%20in%20Varanasi%20in%201920%2C%20Nag%20found%20his%20love%20for%20swimming%20on%20the%20Ganga.%20From%20the%20moment%20he%20surprised%20everyone%20in%20that%20accidental%20race%20in%201930%2C%20he%20competed%20in%20many%20local%20swimming%20competitions%20till%201936%20and%20often%20finished%20in%20the%20first%20two%20positions.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20following%20year%2C%20Jamini%20Das%2C%20a%20well-known%20swimmer%2C%20coach%20and%20captain%20of%20the%20Indian%20water%20polo%20team%20in%20the%201948%20London%20Olympics%2C%20made%20his%20way%20to%20Varanasi%20from%20Kolkata%20(Calcutta).%20Representing%20the%20Calcutta-based%20Hatkhola%20Club%2C%20Das%20was%20accompanied%20by%20young%20swimming%20talent%20who%20had%20come%20to%20compete%20in%20a%20competition%20in%20Varanasi.%20At%20this%20competition%2C%20Das%20saw%20a%20young%20and%20untrained%20Nag%20beat%20the%20best%20his%20club%20had%20to%20offer.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUpon%20witnessing%20this%20talent%2C%20Das%20invited%20Nag%20to%20come%20to%20Calcutta%20and%20train%20with%20him.%20In%20this%20new%20bustling%20city%2C%20the%20young%20Nag%20trained%20with%20the%20club%20and%20stayed%20at%20Das%E2%80%99%20house.%20For%20Nag%2C%20moving%20to%20Calcutta%20was%20the%20break%20he%20needed%20to%20train%20and%20compete%20at%20a%20higher%20level.%20Nag%20began%20training%20and%20competing%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20Hatkhola%20Club%20in%20the%20Bengal%20state%20championships.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESuffice%20it%20to%20say%2C%20he%20beat%20the%20best%20the%20region%20had%20to%20offer%2C%20starting%20with%20the%20100%20m%20and%20400%20m%20freestyle%20events%20in%201938.%20In%20the%20following%20year%2C%20he%20equalled%20the%20national%20record%20for%20the%20100%20m%20freestyle%20event%20with%20a%20time%20of%201%20minute%20and%204%20seconds.%20At%20the%20same%20competition%2C%20he%20broke%20the%20record%20in%20the%20200%20m%20freestyle%20event%20with%20a%20time%20of%202%20minutes%20and%2029%20seconds.%20In%201940%2C%20he%20broke%20the%20100%20m%20freestyle%20record%20set%20by%20fellow%20swimmer%20Dilip%20Mitra%20with%20a%20time%20of%201%20minute%20and%204%20seconds.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20his%20biography%2C%20this%20record%20stood%20for%2031%20years.%20He%20would%20go%20on%20to%20win%20the%20state%20100%20m%20freestyle%20title%20continuously%20for%20nine%20years.%20By%20the%20mid-1940s%2C%20however%2C%20Nag%20began%20harbouring%20dreams%20of%20competing%20on%20a%20world%20stage%2C%20particularly%20the%20London%20Olympics%20of%201948.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ETragedy%20followed%20by%20resilience%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3ETragically%2C%20a%20year%20before%20in%20January%201947%2C%20Nag%20suffered%20a%20serious%20injury%20which%20could%20have%20jeopardised%20his%20chances%20of%20making%20it%20to%20the%20Olympic%20Games.%20This%20was%20a%20time%20of%20great%20violence%20and%20chaos.%20Only%20a%20couple%20of%20months%20earlier%2C%20Calcutta%20had%20witnessed%20bloody%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F218600%2Fdelhi-communal-riots-mumbai-bhiwandi-ips-officer-suresh-khopade-nor41%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecommunal%20riots%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%20isn%E2%80%99t%20much%20evidence%20of%20how%20the%20accident%20actually%20took%20place%2C%20what%20remains%20uncontested%20is%20that%20Nag%20was%20returning%20from%20a%20training%20session%20when%20a%20bullet%20struck%20him%20on%20his%20right%20leg%2C%20shattering%20his%20femur.%20Severely%20injured%2C%20he%20was%20admitted%20to%20a%20hospital%20for%20five%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20he%20was%20discharged%2C%20the%20doctor%20told%20him%20that%20it%20would%20take%20at%20least%20two%20years%20before%20he%20could%20get%20back%20to%20swimming.%20It%20was%20evident%20that%20Nag%E2%80%99s%20chance%20at%20competing%20in%20the%20Olympics%20was%20under%20severe%20jeopardy.%20Determined%20to%20compete%2C%20he%20resumed%20training%20just%20six%20months%20after%20the%20injury.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETo%20facilitate%20his%20recovery%2C%20he%20returned%20to%20his%20family%20in%20Varanasi%20and%20rejoined%20a%20local%20swimming%20club%20while%20getting%20treatment%20from%20local%20masseurs.%20But%20recovering%20from%20a%20serious%20injury%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20the%20only%20hurdle%20he%20had%20to%20overcome.%20Back%20in%20the%20late%201940s%2C%20athletes%20representing%20India%20had%20to%20bear%20a%20great%20deal%20of%20the%20expenses%20required%20to%20compete%20in%20such%20tournaments.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETo%20pay%20for%20his%20trip%20to%20London%2C%20he%20took%20up%20work%20washing%20vehicles%20in%20the%20wee%20hours%20before%20training.%20Despite%20taking%20up%20all%20sorts%20of%20work%2C%20he%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20gather%20the%20requisite%20funds.%20Nag%20was%20about%20to%20give%20up%20on%20his%20dream%20when%20Hemanta%20Mukhopadhyay%2C%20a%20singer%2C%20heard%20about%20his%20plight%20and%20decided%20to%20raise%20funds.%20One%20of%20the%20ways%20in%20which%20the%20singer%20raised%20funds%20was%20through%20a%20musical%20performance%20at%20the%20Uttara%20Cinema%20Hall%20in%20North%20Calcutta.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENag%20finally%20had%20the%20money%20to%20realise%20his%20dream%20of%20competing%20in%20the%20Olympics.%20He%20finished%20in%20sixth%20place%20at%20the%201948%20London%20Olympics%20in%20the%20100%20m%20freestyle%20event.%20What%E2%80%99s%20more%2C%20he%20also%20played%20for%20the%20Indian%20water%20polo%20team%20and%20scored%20four%20goals%20in%20a%207%E2%80%934%20win%20versus%20Chile.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20939px)%20100vw%2C%20939px%5C%22%20src%3D